title: Basic Ontrak Enterprise Setup Guide
content:
First: Review the manual and sales order associated with the install. Identify all points of contact and ensure that you understand the needs to dealer and the end-user.

ADDITIONALLY: Full admin access is required for installation - The program can function without continued admin rights but is not advised.

INSTALLING ONTRAK: DOWNLOADING NEEDED FILES

1. Locate the product page on customers PC: OnTrak Enterprise Truck Scale Data Management
2. After the download is complete, extract the zip file to the downloads folder.

Right click the zip file and locate "Extract All"
Press extract.
3. Locate the folder now in the downloads folder and open it; Then locate the "OntrakEnterprise.Installer.exe"
4. Double click the exe file.
5. In the window that opens press the "I Agree..." checkbox and press install
6. Wait for the installer to complete. Please notice that when the installer gets to the database setup portion (pictured below) it may be "hidden" in the background. Please watch the taskbar for this icon: 


7. Click that icon; in this window simple press connect; ensure it changes to connected, then press "GO"
NOTICE: If there is an existing database with the same name it will present like the picture above with the "Use existing database" selected. Please be sure you select the option you want when reinstalling. If this is a new install you will not have the option to select an existing database.
8. After pressing GO all windows related to the installer will simply disappear - that is good. Any errors need to be handled if they pop up.
9. Navigate in you preferred web browser to: "https://localhost:5000"
10. Press the login button in the top right corner.
11. Minimize the web browser and locate the file explorer. 
12. Enter the "C" Drive root by any means. Locate the "Program Files" directory.
13. Follow the path as such:
C: > Program Files > Rice Lake Weighing Systems > Ontrak Enterprise > secrets
And open the "InitalAdminPassword.txt" - Copy the password in the file.
14. Maximize your web browser from earlier and login with the username: admin@localhost and the password you just copied.
15. Enter a new password.

At this point you must license your Ontrak install to continue with indicator setup - if you are running in demo mode and want some guidance on data creation see this post: NOT DONE

INSTALLING ONTRAK: INDICATOR SETUP
1. In the Ontrak Interface, navigate to the configuration tab
2. Click "Indicators" and press "Create"

3. Select your indicator.

I have selected the 1280 and also opted it in as a Kisok - For more information on setting up a 1280 Kiosk (First finish the indicator setup section here) see this post: NOT DONE
4. Enter the IP Address of your indicator. Standard Rice Lake indicators stay at port 10001. Press "Create".

comments.text:
- Locate the run prompt
	- Press WIN+R
	- Search for it in the Windows Start Menu
- Type %appdata%
- Press OK
- Navigate the folders as such:
>Rice Lake Weighing Systems>Virtui3
- Delete the settings folder and the 3.10 folder.

<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b><span style="font-size:18.0pt;line-height:107%">Assigning Lift ID<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b><o:p> </o:p></b><b style="text-indent: 0.5in; font-size: 1rem;"><u>Locate Lift ID</u></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Locate the Lift ID. This will be stamped on the left cleat.
For older units this will be under the cover on the left-hand side. <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p> </o:p><img src="/uploads/20250724215941_pasted_1753394381420_0.png" class="img-fluid" draggable="true" style="font-size: 1rem;"></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b style="font-size: 1rem;"><u>Assigning
Lift ID using vitui3</u></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">1. Place Jbox into config. <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">2. Connect to lift using virtui3.  <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">3. Once connected go into the calibration menu.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">4. Select two-point calibration.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">5. Once selected, left click in the serial number text box
and enter the lift ID.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">6. Press next on this same page. Once next is pressed the ID
will be assigned.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape

</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">7. Confirm that the Lift ID was entered properly, leaving
and re-entering into two-point calibration. If entered correctly the Serial
Number should be displayed. <o:p></o:p></p>
